teriorly and pars plicata posteriorly with pars plana secreting aqueous humour","Pars plana posteriorly and pars plicata anteriorly with pars plana secreting aqueous humour","Single zone of pars plicata that secretes aqueous humour"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe ciliary body consists of two distinct zones. The \u003Cstrong\u003Epars plana posteriorly and pars plicata anteriorly with pars plicata secreting aqueous humour\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct anatomical arrangement. The pars plicata contains the ciliary processes which are responsible for aqueous humour production.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe arrangement described in \u003Cstrong\u003Epars plana anteriorly and pars plicata posteriorly with pars plicata secreting aqueous humour\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as it reverses the anatomical positions. Similarly, stating that the \u003Cstrong\u003Epars plana anteriorly and pars plicata posteriorly with pars plana secreting aqueous humour\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect both anatomically and functionally.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe option \u003Cstrong\u003Epars plana posteriorly and pars plicata anteriorly with pars plana secreting aqueous humour\u003C/strong\u003E has correct anatomical positioning but incorrect function. Finally, describing a \u003Cstrong\u003Esingle zone of pars plicata that secretes aqueous humour\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as it fails to acknowledge the two-zone structure of the ciliary body.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The ciliary body consists of two zones: pars plicata anteriorly and pars plana posteriorly.","The pars plicata contains ciliary processes that actively secrete aqueous humour into the posterior chamber of the eye.","The pars plana is a flatter region that forms the posterior portion of the ciliary body."],"references":["Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier 